description.narrative: UNICEF alongside the coalition “Child Right Now”, NGOs and EU contributed to put child rights issues in the political and public agenda during the CRC@30 that allowed 221 children from the fourteen regions to voice and propose actions-recommendations on child rights during the media take over. Overall in 2019, UNICEF's visibility trough Facebook, twitter and video has increased from 1.059.476 in 2018 to 1,347,969 in 2019. C4D Health communication platform that brings together communication focal points from the MSAS, civil society, FTP and NGOs programs has been revitalized while C4D capacity building across institutions, media and children has been pursued. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
